{{Quote|He has resisted conventional interrogations, poisons, even the Force. But the Sith torture mask has kept him from regaining focus, and his body is weak.|[[Asajj Ventress/Legends|Asajj Ventress]]|<ref name="Republic 60">[[Republic 60|''Republic'' 60]]</ref>}}
A '''Sith [[Torture/Legends|torture]] mask''' was a hood used by the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] when interrogating [[Prisoner/Legends|prisoners]], especially [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]]. The prisoner would be forced to wear the mask, which was both unremarkable to behold and covered the entire head except the [[Eye/Legends|eyes]]. This allowed the captured being to see what was happening to them. While resembling ordinary masks, the torture mask was actually imbued with [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] energy preventing [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] from calling upon [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] by stopping them from concentrating.

[[Asajj Ventress/Legends|Asajj Ventress]] kept a Sith torture mask in [[Castle Ventress]] on [[Rattatak/Legends|Rattatak]], where she used it on [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] following the [[Battle of Jabiim]].

